title: For Sale:  Hk Heckler Koch MR556 Upper
postcontent:
For Sale BNIB a hk mr 556 upper, this item is brand new never assembled or fired. 
The MR556A1 Upper Receiver Kit includes a complete upper receiver/ barrel assembly, bolt carrier assembly, buffer, and buffer spring allowing Mil-Spec 5.56 mm AR-style rifles to be retrofitted to HK’s pusher rod system. The Upper Receiver Kit is the core of the HK 5.56 mm proprietary gas piston operating system. It employs a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms.

The same operating system is used in the combat-proven 5.56 mm HK416 as well as the G36, HK417, and a variety of other Heckler & Koch arms. The MR556A1 Upper Receiver Kit is designed to be fully interchangeable with all high quality AR-style firearms, simply by attaching it to an AR lower receiver using the standard takedown pins. Due to the shortened length of the HK buffer and HK (action) buffer spring, these parts do not work in fixed stock AR-type rifles. Installation of MIL-SPEC hammers in non-HK lower receivers are required for reliable function. Additionally, the MR556A1 Upper Receiver Kit does not work in lower receivers with fully automatic or selective fire mechanisms. However, the HK416 Upper Receiver Kit (available to military and law enforcement customers) is designed to function with fully automatic and selective fire lower receivers. The HK piston driven operating system virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers. Designed to function with a wide variety of high quality 5.56 x 45 mm ammunition, the MR556A1 Upper Receiver Kit uses a C.I.P. dimensioned chamber (a chamber with dimensions specified by the Commission Internationale Permanente).

The MR556A1 also functions reliably with most quality Caliber .223 Remington ammunition. The MR556A1 Upper Receiver Kit is produced in the USA using American and German made components. The Upper Receiver Kit uses a German-made barrel manufactured by Heckler & Koch’s famous cold hammer forging technology. The highest quality steel is used in this unique manufacturing process creating a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life.

The unchromed 16.5-inch barrel has an internal profile of 6 lands and grooves with a 1 in 7 inch (178 mm) twist. It is also moderately “swagged” with a slightly smaller internal diameter at the muzzle end than the chamber end. This feature has a positive effect on bullet accuracy and velocity. A thick, heavy contour also contributes to its excellent accuracy. The Upper Receiver Kit also includes the HK Free Floating Rail System (FFRS) handguard with its four MIL-STD-1913 “Picatinny” rails. This premium machined alloy handguard allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero when reinstalled. The Upper Receiver Kit also has a Picantinny rail machined into the top of its upper receiver for mounting optics and mechanical sights.

HK MR556 Upper kit includes:
Complete MR556 Upper Receiver/Barrel Assembly HK 16.5 inch cold-hammer forged barrel, upper receiver with forward assist, extended convertible charging handle, HK Free Floating Rail System handguard 
Complete MR556 Bolt Group Assembly 
HK Proprietary Buffer

postcontent:
Everything in the picture is included, to include the gun case which will hold all of this.
On the top half of the case is a Stag Arms 6.8 upper and lower. The lower has an ambidextrous single point sling adapter and a single point sling. The upper has the free float forend, and a nickel boron bolt carrier group. I pulled it out in the pic so you can see how clean they keep. They dont get any carbon build up on them at all. The optics is a 3-9x50 basic scope zeroed in at 200yds. Its not a super high end scope, but ARs dont kick like mules either. It has been holding up to the 6.8 recoil for around 200 rounds that Ive put down it. It comes with 2 magazines stamped 6.8 and 1 box of Hornady 6.8 ammo.
The lower half of the gun case is a DPMS 5.56/.223 upper with 1:9 twist. It has quad rail forend with all the rail adapters to put over the rails if you want to use them. Also comes with a fold down foregrip attached to it. Standard bolt carrier in it also. The light is a surefire millenium universal ($350) with the M93 mounting base $175(quick release) and the KM3 light head $250 on it (switches between white light and infrared). It comes with a NcStar 4x32 scope that has a red laser on it as well and has the quick detach/attach lever. I have 2 new in the box GI style mags, 2 used mags, 3x20rd boxes of ammo, and a bag of loose reloaded ammo leftover from a box I got at a gun show last year.
The 5.56 upper will mount to the 6.8 lower perfectly and will take the 5.56 mags as well. Basically 2 uppers and 1 lower to make 2 different caliber rifles. I target shoot here and there with the 5.56 and used the 6.8 to hunt hogs in TX, although I did drop a doe with it a few weeks ago.
The entire set up was almost $2500 BEFORE the stupid rise in value of these 'assault' rifles. The surefire alone was over $500. So that being said, NO, $2000 will not come close. $3500 obo

For the right price, I'll also throw in my Smith and Wesson M&P 15-22. Excellent shape, no mods. Comes with the box and manuals and fold down grip.

I require a bill of sale to be done on this rifle which means I will ask you for your name, phone number, and DLN in order to prove you are an Arkansas resident. If you are unwilling to give any of these up, please don't offer to purchase the rifle. Thank you!
